<br>
First of all, I would take mez over root any day. In fact I'll be very pissed if they change the mez to root. Mages are the masters of summoned creature, it makes much more sense imho that we be able to put them to sleep, much more than rooting them, wich is nature magic (druid turf). For me it would be a huge nerf if they made the mez spell become a root spell. Mez &gt; root, summoned only mez make sense, wtf ask for root? I don't get it. Mages that have been asking for root for ages obviously have no clue about how strong mages would be with root (talking about regular root here, spell that work only VS summoned are VERY situational). I want my mez, screw the root idea. =D<br>
<br>
